.\" termin.al-name: whoami
.\" termin.al-usage: whoami
.\" termin.al-summary: Show the current development capability.
.TH WHOAMI 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
whoami \- Show the current development capability.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
whoami
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints the fixed capability identity used by the public browser demo.
.SH OUTPUT
The exact output is
.BR anonymous .
It describes the current unauthenticated development capability, not an operating-system account, GitHub identity or browser profile.
.SH FAILURES
Any argument is rejected.
.SH NOTES
The value is not read from credentials or browser storage and is unchanged by the unavailable login and logout commands.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ whoami
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
login(1), logout(1), stats(1)
